        "settings_privacy_policy_body" to "DeviceDNA reads hardware, OS, battery, storage, network, sensor, camera metadata, installed app inventory, and health diagnostics to show them in the app. Some data stays local, including settings, widget state, battery intelligence history, exported reports until you share them, and the encrypted offline Premium cache. If you sign in or use sync, DeviceDNA transmits your Firebase account identifier, Android ID, device summary, diagnostics snapshot, sync timestamps, and Premium status to the DeviceDNA backend on Cloudflare and Neon. Google sign-in uses Firebase Authentication. Real Premium purchases use Google Play Billing and backend verification with Google Play. Ads may be served by Google Mobile Ads. Public IP lookup contacts api.ipify.org only when enabled. Sensitive identifiers are masked by default; camera permission is used for camera/flashlight tests and no photos or videos are recorded. DeviceDNA does not sell personal or sensitive data. Backend data is retained while needed for sync, account checks, subscription verification, fraud prevention, service operation, or legal compliance. You can sign out, disable public IP lookup, keep IMEI/serial hidden, reduce background monitoring, revoke Android permissions, clear local app data, uninstall the app, or request backend data deletion through the developer contact in the Google Play listing.",
